caption.text: I have to tell you all something,... I just landed my first paid photography gig!!! Woo Hoo - not in a million years would I ever thought someone would pay me to take pictures. You guys can't see it right now, but Im bouncing off the walls of my house at this moment. Lately, I've been posting some of my pictures on the different social networking sites that I belong to. Well somebody noticed my photographs, and asked me to document their wedding. How wild is that!? Of course I jumped on the opportunity. However, the problem is that I've never shot anything like like a wedding before. To tell you the truth, I don't even know the first thing about photographing a wedding. Maybe I'll consult with my artsy friend who had her entire wedding shot with two Holgas? I think those were the best wedding pictures I've ever seen. However, I doubt this couple is into anything that untraditional but they obviously want something different if they chose me to photograph their wedding. I have some time to figure it out, because the wedding isn't until October. I suppose gratitude is in order, because if it wasn't for all your likes, comments, and follows I doubt I would have ever picked up my camera again. So from the bottom of my heart I say, thank you. Now I have to stop by the library and check out a book on how to photograph weddings. Wish me luck.  #bwwednesday
